headline: 'Corporate America Got Lost With Idiot Management And Inability To Read The Room,' Says Kevin O'Leary, Citing Target And Anheuser-Busch
summary: In a recent interview with FOX Business, Kevin O’Leary, a well-known business owner and investor, discussed the mistakes made by big companies in America. He pointed out Target (NYSE:TGT) and Anheuser-Busch (NYSE:BUD) as examples of what he called “idiot management” and a complete “inability to read the room.” O’Leary said these brands didn’t listen to their customers – and paid the price for it.
